headline: Klarna Sinks Below IPO Price as Fintech Competition Heats Up
summary: Klarna started trading on Sept. 10 after the company and some of its backers raised about $1.58 billion in an offering that was double-digit oversubscribed and priced above the marketed range.  “Fintech stocks, including Klarna, are sensitive to macroeconomic factors like interest rates and regulatory developments,” said Diksha Gera, a Bloomberg Intelligence analyst.
